1
00:03:50,986 --> 00:03:53,823
Chanwoo, I'm so glad you came.

2
00:03:55,491 --> 00:03:56,617
I'm here.

3
00:03:57,368 --> 00:03:58,661
I won't leave you.

4
00:04:08,707 --> 00:04:09,917
Do you love me?

5
00:04:12,619 --> 00:04:13,619
I love you.

6
00:04:34,521 --> 00:04:36,401
I've been calling
you for a while.

7
00:04:36,901 --> 00:04:38,277
Angel is already downstairs.

8
00:04:38,277 --> 00:04:39,570
She’s been calling you too.

9
00:04:39,570 --> 00:04:40,613
But you weren’t answering.

10
00:04:43,601 --> 00:04:44,853
Oh, right.

11
00:04:46,799 --> 00:04:48,931
What are you buying again, huh?

12
00:04:48,955 --> 00:04:51,492
What are you buying now,
more K-pop stuff?

13
00:04:51,505 --> 00:04:53,585
Oh my, no wonder you
don’t have any savings.

14
00:04:53,586 --> 00:04:56,338
With all the things you're buying
that aren’t even important.

15
00:04:56,338 --> 00:04:58,009
That’s another
concert ticket, isn’t it?

16
00:04:59,258 --> 00:05:00,509
Oh, Melody.

17
00:05:00,509 --> 00:05:01,778
That’s expensive again.

18
00:05:01,802 --> 00:05:03,262
It’s not that expensive, Ma.

19
00:05:03,262 --> 00:05:09,398
And Chanwoo only comes here once,
so for me, this is important.

20
00:05:09,422 --> 00:05:11,270
I’m telling you, Melody.

21
00:05:11,270 --> 00:05:12,438
Save up.

22
00:05:12,612 --> 00:05:15,190
Don’t be like me who
didn’t save anything before.

23
00:05:16,114 --> 00:05:17,282
This is the last one, Ma,
I promise.

24
00:05:17,282 --> 00:05:19,617
I’ll save up after this concert.

25
00:05:19,617 --> 00:05:20,617
Okay, Ma?

26
00:05:26,308 --> 00:05:27,308
My child.

27
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:30,712
Can you really save with all
that freelancing you’re doing?

28
00:05:31,090 --> 00:05:32,883
Get a real job already.

29
00:05:33,770 --> 00:05:35,814
My job is real, Ma.

30
00:05:36,616 --> 00:05:39,380
Isn’t it better that I work
from home all the time?

31
00:05:40,783 --> 00:05:44,245
And staying up late like
that isn’t good for you.

32
00:05:44,662 --> 00:05:47,665
You keep watching videos
of your Korean guy.

33
00:05:48,700 --> 00:05:49,700
Okay, Ma.

34
00:05:50,207 --> 00:05:53,335
I’ll apply for a job
after this concert.

35
00:05:53,544 --> 00:05:55,898
You won't sweet talk your
way out of me, Melody.

36
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:58,969
You’re just saying that
so I won’t get mad, right?

37
00:05:59,344 --> 00:06:00,344
I’m serious, Ma.

38
00:06:00,554 --> 00:06:03,372
George said there’s an opening.

39
00:06:03,386 --> 00:06:04,727
I’ll give it a shot.

40
00:06:05,119 --> 00:06:08,008
So please don’t be mad, Ma.

41
00:06:08,032 --> 00:06:10,286
Please don’t be mad.

42
00:06:26,410 --> 00:06:27,410
Yes!

43
00:06:27,434 --> 00:06:28,495
Work is done!

44
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:30,307
It’s bebe time!

45
00:06:30,317 --> 00:06:31,776
Hello, Chanwoo!

46
00:06:31,776 --> 00:06:34,185
Chanwoo! Chanwoo! Chanwoo!

47
00:06:36,807 --> 00:06:38,058
I’m sorry.

48
00:06:38,058 --> 00:06:39,542
I’m sorry, Chanwoo.

49
00:06:39,566 --> 00:06:41,026
I took so long.

50
00:06:41,050 --> 00:06:42,260
I was still working.

51
00:06:42,267 --> 00:06:43,602
You know, so I can...

52
00:06:43,860 --> 00:06:45,611
so I can support you.

53
00:06:48,155 --> 00:06:49,155
Okay.

54
00:06:50,062 --> 00:06:51,939
Parasocial relationship.

55
00:06:52,582 --> 00:06:56,460
This is what they call the
feeling fans have for a celebrity.

56
00:06:57,947 --> 00:06:59,949
Even if you don’t
really know them,

57
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:02,242
it feels like you
know them so well.

58
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:06,391
But it’s also sad to think
because all of this is one-sided.

59
00:07:29,038 --> 00:07:32,017
Chanwoo, I'm so glad you came.

60
00:07:32,041 --> 00:07:33,167
I'm here.

61
00:07:33,918 --> 00:07:35,251
I won't leave you.

62
00:07:55,298 --> 00:07:56,299
Do you love me?

63
00:07:56,675 --> 00:07:57,675
I love you.

64
00:08:00,887 --> 00:08:02,806
Their coffee really
tastes so good.

65
00:08:03,181 --> 00:08:04,808
I swear,
I have nothing bad to say.

66
00:08:13,233 --> 00:08:17,246
I think I'm energized enough
to go back to Bebe time.

67
00:08:18,633 --> 00:08:20,480
I hope we get tickets, right?

68
00:08:20,504 --> 00:08:22,980
We will.
Your tablet is fast anyway.

69
00:08:22,993 --> 00:08:24,504
My laptop is trash.

70
00:08:24,673 --> 00:08:26,049
So we’ll definitely get tickets.

71
00:08:26,049 --> 00:08:28,635
There it is!
It’s about to start!

72
00:08:28,927 --> 00:08:30,721
- This is so stressful.
- Hey, come on.

73
00:08:30,721 --> 00:08:32,531
Just relax!
Do your best, girl!

74
00:08:32,556 --> 00:08:34,199
There it is, there it is!
Click, click!

75
00:08:34,224 --> 00:08:35,449
Click it, click it!

76
00:08:35,473 --> 00:08:36,892
VIP! VIP! VIP!

77
00:08:39,484 --> 00:08:41,520
Uhh, ah, upper box! Upper box.

78
00:08:41,999 --> 00:08:43,592
There, go, go.

79
00:08:44,259 --> 00:08:45,677
- Okay go.
- It’s gone too.

80
00:08:48,991 --> 00:08:50,705
No, wait. Maybe there’s
still some on the other side.

81
00:08:51,406 --> 00:08:53,909
The others.
The lower box, lower box.

82
00:08:57,267 --> 00:08:59,102
There’s none left.

83
00:09:00,007 --> 00:09:02,134
Oh, what happened?

84
00:09:02,843 --> 00:09:04,887
There’s none left,
it says sold out, Ma.

85
00:09:05,304 --> 00:09:07,449
What does that mean? All gone?

86
00:09:07,473 --> 00:09:09,016
Yes, it’s all gone.

87
00:09:09,933 --> 00:09:13,090
Fifteen thousand seats,
and we still didn’t get one.

88
00:09:13,096 --> 00:09:14,347
Hi, Tita!

89
00:09:17,637 --> 00:09:20,473
Oh, what are those faces?

90
00:09:21,017 --> 00:09:22,309
The tickets were sold out.

91
00:09:24,001 --> 00:09:26,754
You know what,
just go eat instead.

92
00:09:27,690 --> 00:09:29,191
What time is it even?

93
00:09:29,525 --> 00:09:31,527
Didn’t the ticket
selling just start?

94
00:09:31,527 --> 00:09:34,279
You know, not even one second passed
and it was already sold out!

95
00:09:34,303 --> 00:09:35,972
It was all so fast!

96
00:09:35,972 --> 00:09:37,056
Right?!

97
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:42,016
That’s exactly why I bought gelato,
because I had a feeling,

98
00:09:42,391 --> 00:09:43,684
you wouldn’t be
able to get tickets.

99
00:09:43,934 --> 00:09:45,394
You’re so mean!

100
00:09:45,978 --> 00:09:48,000
You manifested that
we wouldn’t get any?

101
00:09:48,856 --> 00:09:49,856
Oh, you don’t want it?

102
00:09:50,149 --> 00:09:51,609
Fine, I’ll just take this home.

103
00:09:52,202 --> 00:09:53,870
Oh, give it to me,
give it to me. I’ll eat it.

104
00:09:54,602 --> 00:09:56,137
What’s that gelato?

105
00:09:56,142 --> 00:09:57,644
It’s like ice cream, Tita.

106
00:09:58,122 --> 00:09:59,122
This is good.

107
00:09:59,331 --> 00:10:00,875
There’s one here for you.

108
00:10:03,002 --> 00:10:04,837
Don’t be sad about it.

109
00:10:05,254 --> 00:10:07,798
That’s actually good,
you’ll be able to save up now.

110
00:10:08,591 --> 00:10:09,925
Buy a laptop instead.

111
00:10:11,594 --> 00:10:13,596
I can’t believe it.

112
00:10:14,805 --> 00:10:16,240
Is there really none left?

113
00:10:16,608 --> 00:10:17,942
Check again, Angel.

114
00:10:20,537 --> 00:10:23,308
There’s really none left,
it’s sold out.

115
00:10:24,521 --> 00:10:25,856
What am I supposed to do now?

116
00:10:26,208 --> 00:10:28,502
How will Chanwoo
even notice me now?

117
00:10:28,961 --> 00:10:30,546
Why would he notice you?

118
00:10:31,797 --> 00:10:33,006
And why wouldn’t he?

119
00:10:33,296 --> 00:10:35,468
Your daughter is so
delulu, Tita Esther.

120
00:10:36,196 --> 00:10:37,239
What’s “delulu”?

121
00:10:37,239 --> 00:10:38,615
He's saying i'm delusional, Ma.

122
00:10:44,904 --> 00:10:46,437
I remember, it hurts!

123
00:10:46,904 --> 00:10:47,904
It hurts!

124
00:10:48,530 --> 00:10:58,158
🎶I love to see the ocean's beauty
And the moon that shines above🎶

125
00:10:58,163 --> 00:11:00,451
There you go again
with that song.

126
00:11:00,785 --> 00:11:03,871
You know, you’ve already played
that a thousand times this week.

127
00:11:04,205 --> 00:11:06,499
It's actually two thousand times already.

128
00:11:06,832 --> 00:11:09,728
This is the most
beautiful song in the world.

129
00:11:09,752 --> 00:11:11,930
And this is the
song that helped me.

130
00:11:11,954 --> 00:11:15,883
Whenever I hear it,
I feel like he knows me.

131
00:11:16,203 --> 00:11:17,203
That’s true, right?

132
00:11:17,223 --> 00:11:19,179
Yeah, he knows you so well.

133
00:11:19,203 --> 00:11:20,513
That’s why you
don’t have a ticket.

134
00:11:20,538 --> 00:11:22,515
You’re so mean.
You’re such a mood killer.

135
00:11:22,988 --> 00:11:25,824
You know, someday,
I’ll hear this live.

136
00:11:25,824 --> 00:11:28,076
And then, he’ll turn around.

137
00:11:28,535 --> 00:11:32,206
And then he’ll realize that
I’m his number one fan.

138
00:11:32,206 --> 00:11:34,041
Mark my words, okay?

139
00:11:34,045 --> 00:11:35,397
That’s impossible.

140
00:11:35,421 --> 00:11:39,073
Fifteen thousand seats got sold out,
and he’ll look at you?

141
00:11:40,205 --> 00:11:41,205
Shut up already.

142
00:11:41,918 --> 00:11:43,711
You’re so sensitive.

143
00:11:44,318 --> 00:11:45,913
I was just joking.

144
00:11:47,779 --> 00:11:50,199
That’s not something
to joke about.

145
00:11:51,491 --> 00:11:53,410
You already know that’s
the only thing I want.

146
00:11:53,811 --> 00:11:54,854
And you still joke about it.

147
00:11:54,854 --> 00:11:56,007
Now my mood is ruined.

148
00:11:56,031 --> 00:11:57,440
I didn’t even get a ticket.

149
00:11:57,440 --> 00:11:58,566
And then you treat me like that.

150
00:11:59,838 --> 00:12:00,838
How about this instead.

151
00:12:02,382 --> 00:12:05,260
We can still wait outside
the concert hall, right?

152
00:12:05,797 --> 00:12:07,216
Maybe he’ll come out.

153
00:12:07,617 --> 00:12:09,744
Or maybe we’ll see his car.

154
00:12:11,189 --> 00:12:12,189
That’s right!

155
00:12:13,311 --> 00:12:14,938
You’re right!

156
00:12:15,824 --> 00:12:16,908
- Let’s wait for him.
- Let’s go!

157
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,660
Come with us, you
and Angel, if ever.

158
00:12:18,660 --> 00:12:19,744
Sure, okay.

159
00:12:21,621 --> 00:12:25,542
George, what was that job
you were telling Melody?

160
00:12:25,542 --> 00:12:27,544
Maybe she can
apply there already.

161
00:12:28,211 --> 00:12:30,085
She might end up jobless.

162
00:12:30,109 --> 00:12:31,109
Jobless?

163
00:12:31,819 --> 00:12:32,987
I do have a job, Ma.

164
00:12:32,987 --> 00:12:34,613
You should still apply there.

165
00:12:34,874 --> 00:12:36,333
George, please
take care of it, son.

166
00:12:36,333 --> 00:12:37,585
Yes, Tita.

167
00:12:38,002 --> 00:12:42,423
I think the position my
contact mentioned is still open.

168
00:12:42,631 --> 00:12:45,050
That’s a sign that you
couldn’t get a ticket

169
00:12:45,050 --> 00:12:47,887
so you should stop obsessing
over your Korean stuff.

170
00:12:48,554 --> 00:12:49,554
Yes, Ma.

171
00:12:51,724 --> 00:12:53,095
- Let's wait for him.
- Here's yours.

172
00:12:53,119 --> 00:12:54,119
Thank you.

173
00:12:55,001 --> 00:12:56,651
- What flavor did you get?
- There, a spoon.

174
00:12:59,219 --> 00:13:01,263
Well, that's basically it.

175
00:13:01,552 --> 00:13:03,783
Thank you for meeting
me here, Melody.

176
00:13:04,104 --> 00:13:07,565
I'm sorry that we had to
hold this interview off-site.

177
00:13:07,589 --> 00:13:11,444
Our whole team is currently out
of the office with a couple of clients.

178
00:13:11,444 --> 00:13:15,212
So, we're basically working
out of our bags right now.

179
00:13:15,237 --> 00:13:16,300
That’s okay, Ma’am.

180
00:13:16,324 --> 00:13:17,325
No problem.

181
00:13:17,951 --> 00:13:21,538
I appreciate your flexibility
but just to be clear.

182
00:13:21,830 --> 00:13:25,680
If you will get this position,
most of your work will be like this.

183
00:13:25,917 --> 00:13:30,005
Out of the office, on-site at venues,
and joining tour events.

184
00:13:30,380 --> 00:13:32,173
This is not a typical desk job.

185
00:13:32,340 --> 00:13:33,633
Do you think you
can handle that?

186
00:13:35,969 --> 00:13:36,969
Yes.

187
00:13:37,929 --> 00:13:38,972
That's good to hear.

188
00:13:38,972 --> 00:13:43,059
Well, we will contact you
via email for the results.

189
00:13:43,393 --> 00:13:44,686
And thank you for your time.

190
00:13:44,686 --> 00:13:45,687
I'll go ahead.

191
00:13:45,687 --> 00:13:48,189
And you can stay here to
finish your food and drinks.

192
00:13:48,189 --> 00:13:49,621
But I really need to go.

193
00:13:49,858 --> 00:13:51,498
Okay? Thank you, Melody.

194
00:13:51,522 --> 00:13:52,776
Oh. Thank you.

195
00:14:05,081 --> 00:14:06,081
Hot!

196
00:14:15,770 --> 00:14:16,938
Hello, ugly!

197
00:14:17,523 --> 00:14:19,442
What’s up?
I just finished my interview!

198
00:14:25,794 --> 00:14:27,254
Where are you now, ugly?

199
00:14:27,807 --> 00:14:28,933
Are you ready, George?

200
00:14:30,314 --> 00:14:31,314
Yes.

201
00:14:42,433 --> 00:14:43,910
Uh, hi, everyone.

202
00:14:43,934 --> 00:14:45,728
My name is George Villoria.

203
00:14:46,312 --> 00:14:50,399
And the first song I’ll be
singing is a personal story.

204
00:14:52,693 --> 00:14:56,312
It’s not finished yet because
we still don’t have an ending.

205
00:14:56,819 --> 00:14:59,905
But I just want to
share it with all of you.

206
00:15:00,466 --> 00:15:02,176
This song is called, Kalawakan.

207
00:15:31,997 --> 00:15:37,770
🎶Going in circles, round and
round in my heart, in my mind🎶

208
00:15:38,045 --> 00:15:41,149
🎶You’re the only one inside🎶

209
00:15:43,901 --> 00:15:47,988
🎶My gaze stays fixed on you🎶

210
00:15:48,012 --> 00:15:52,660
🎶I can feel the signs🎶

211
00:15:52,684 --> 00:15:54,954
[Congratulations! You got the job!]

212
00:15:54,978 --> 00:15:57,706
[Congratulations! You got the job!]
Yes. But...

213
00:15:58,541 --> 00:16:01,794
my days as a full-time
fangirl are over.

214
00:16:02,806 --> 00:16:04,725
The universe
answered me so fast.

215
00:16:07,175 --> 00:16:16,601
🎶I just hope you tell
me what you feel🎶

216
00:16:16,626 --> 00:16:20,271
🎶Maybe you could give a chance🎶

217
00:16:21,397 --> 00:16:24,032
🎶To what my heart feels...🎶
- Confidential.

218
00:16:24,859 --> 00:16:28,613
The brand is hiring you
to research on Chanwoo?!

219
00:16:28,617 --> 00:16:31,699
Chanwoo's Philippine fanbase
will present a Brand Collab.

220
00:16:31,866 --> 00:16:33,242
Strategy of your first—

221
00:16:33,242 --> 00:16:35,244
Oh my gosh.

222
00:16:35,604 --> 00:16:36,604
Wait?

223
00:16:37,147 --> 00:16:38,147
Brand collab?

224
00:16:39,107 --> 00:16:40,692
So Chanwoo is my client?!

225
00:16:40,716 --> 00:16:41,878
Chanwoo—

226
00:16:41,902 --> 00:16:43,795
Chanwoo is my client!

227
00:16:44,070 --> 00:16:46,255
What kind of sign
is this, universe?

228
00:16:46,573 --> 00:16:47,949
I was already about to give up!

229
00:16:47,949 --> 00:16:49,717
I already accepted it.

230
00:16:50,760 --> 00:16:54,269
So this is a sign.
I should love Chanwoo even more!

231
00:16:54,275 --> 00:16:56,305
🎶...maybe you could give a chance🎶

232
00:16:56,329 --> 00:16:57,442
Okay.
🎶...maybe you could give a chance🎶

233
00:16:57,466 --> 00:16:58,696
I'm so proud of myself.

234
00:16:58,720 --> 00:17:04,732
🎶My heart that only
knows how to love🎶

235
00:17:04,741 --> 00:17:13,032
🎶We’ll reach the vast universe🎶

236
00:17:13,908 --> 00:17:16,744
Relax, Melody, relax.
Melody, not yet.

237
00:17:20,957 --> 00:17:22,292
Cheers!

238
00:17:22,292 --> 00:17:23,292
Wow.

239
00:17:26,253 --> 00:17:27,505
Congrats, ugly.

240
00:17:27,505 --> 00:17:29,965
You got so many cheers
and requests earlier.

241
00:17:30,667 --> 00:17:33,469
I don’t think you even watched
my original composition,

242
00:17:33,493 --> 00:17:34,691
the first song I sang,

243
00:17:34,715 --> 00:17:35,722
- Ahhh.
- did you hear it?

244
00:17:35,746 --> 00:17:36,792
Sorry.

245
00:17:36,812 --> 00:17:38,731
I was distracted earlier.

246
00:17:38,731 --> 00:17:42,228
But the songs you performed after that,
I already knew.

247
00:17:42,512 --> 00:17:44,013
Why were you distracted?

248
00:17:45,014 --> 00:17:46,014
Nothing.

249
00:17:46,349 --> 00:17:48,851
I got accepted to the
job you recommended.

250
00:17:49,083 --> 00:17:50,083
Really?

251
00:17:50,094 --> 00:17:52,130
- You got accepted?
- Mhmm!

252
00:17:52,154 --> 00:17:55,199
Wow, my best friend.

253
00:17:56,283 --> 00:17:57,366
You know, it’s okay.

254
00:17:57,390 --> 00:18:00,727
Even if you can’t
fangirl as much anymore,

255
00:18:00,727 --> 00:18:03,068
at least you’ll have
a new routine again.

256
00:18:03,092 --> 00:18:04,092
That’s right.

257
00:18:04,117 --> 00:18:06,452
You’ll be able to save up—
for your new laptop!

258
00:18:06,452 --> 00:18:07,461
Right.

259
00:18:07,464 --> 00:18:09,591
So don’t be sad about it.

260
00:18:09,804 --> 00:18:11,097
What are you saying, George?

261
00:18:11,097 --> 00:18:12,300
I’m not sad.

262
00:18:12,311 --> 00:18:13,312
You know why?

263
00:18:14,188 --> 00:18:17,567
Because I’ll be working
with Chanwoo!

264
00:18:19,098 --> 00:18:20,474
That’s crazy, that’s crazy.

265
00:18:20,738 --> 00:18:23,032
Even if I didn’t get
his concert ticket,

266
00:18:23,032 --> 00:18:24,802
I’ll get closer to him instead.

267
00:18:24,826 --> 00:18:26,160
Can you believe it?
That’s insane!

268
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:27,662
What kind of sign is this?!

269
00:18:29,831 --> 00:18:31,958
Wow. You’re unbelievable.

270
00:18:31,958 --> 00:18:33,060
Right?

271
00:18:33,084 --> 00:18:36,691
But you know,
all of this is because of you.

272
00:18:37,088 --> 00:18:38,590
So, thank you, ugly.

273
00:18:39,299 --> 00:18:41,926
For pushing me to apply here.

274
00:18:42,343 --> 00:18:43,706
That’s why you’re
my best friend!

275
00:18:44,387 --> 00:18:45,447
Best friend.

276
00:18:45,471 --> 00:18:48,433
Yes. Best, best, best friend.

277
00:18:49,809 --> 00:18:50,851
Congrats, ugly.

278
00:18:51,182 --> 00:18:52,182
I'm happy for you.

279
00:18:52,350 --> 00:18:53,350
Thank you.

280
00:18:53,727 --> 00:18:55,145
But I’m so excited.

281
00:19:18,168 --> 00:19:21,588
I've been reviewing your
initial reports, Melody.

282
00:19:21,588 --> 00:19:24,090
And I must say, I'm so proud.

283
00:19:24,282 --> 00:19:31,355
Your insights about the fan behavior
and Chanwoo's fanbase are so detailed.

284
00:19:31,379 --> 00:19:32,589
Thank you, ma’am.

285
00:19:32,791 --> 00:19:36,211
I just made sure that our data
is accurate for the strategy.

286
00:19:36,503 --> 00:19:39,220
You know so much
about fangirling culture.

287
00:19:39,506 --> 00:19:46,853
And the details about the past of
Chanwoo's schedule and preferences.

288
00:19:47,889 --> 00:19:52,227
I'm thinking, Melody,
are you a fan of Chanwoo?

289
00:19:53,497 --> 00:19:58,906
Ah, I just researched
very hard for this project.

290
00:19:59,112 --> 00:20:02,061
To understand the market, yes.

291
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:03,384
Good.

292
00:20:03,408 --> 00:20:05,621
Because work is work, Melody.

293
00:20:06,202 --> 00:20:08,848
And fangirling is
not allowed on site.

294
00:20:09,247 --> 00:20:11,960
Most especially,
we will be having the performances.

295
00:20:12,542 --> 00:20:16,879
So tell me, Melody,
what is the vibe of our first content?

296
00:20:16,879 --> 00:20:18,506
Oh, first content, yeah.

297
00:20:19,132 --> 00:20:24,063
So, based on my research,
we need to make it relatable to the masses.

298
00:21:04,696 --> 00:21:06,307
- Oh, Chanwoo.
- Annyeonghaseyo.

299
00:21:06,609 --> 00:21:08,027
- Annyeonghaseyo.
- How are you?

300
00:21:08,027 --> 00:21:10,321
I'm good.
Is it okay if I sit here?

301
00:21:13,394 --> 00:21:14,809
Sure, Melody.

302
00:21:14,839 --> 00:21:16,900
Oh, sir. Here.
Sit here, sit here.

303
00:21:16,924 --> 00:21:18,265
Okay, here's the chair for you.

304
00:21:41,133 --> 00:21:42,133
Are you okay?

305
00:21:42,990 --> 00:21:44,116
I'm fine.

306
00:21:44,141 --> 00:21:45,142
Please move.

307
00:21:47,937 --> 00:21:49,063
Can we resume in a few minutes?

308
00:21:49,063 --> 00:21:50,606
I just need to go
to the washroom.

309
00:21:51,315 --> 00:21:52,315
Okay.

310
00:22:06,467 --> 00:22:07,467
Okay.

311
00:22:08,202 --> 00:22:09,202
Relax.

312
00:22:09,954 --> 00:22:11,622
I’ll just use some
White Rose Papaya.

313
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:25,511
Operation "Glow Up."

314
00:22:26,512 --> 00:22:29,532
Manifesting that my
crush notices me again.

315
00:23:33,329 --> 00:23:34,330
Let me eat first.

316
00:23:36,836 --> 00:23:38,212
Is George not here yet?

317
00:23:38,849 --> 00:23:40,225
He’s taking so long.

318
00:23:40,935 --> 00:23:42,311
What time is it?

319
00:23:47,983 --> 00:23:48,983
So good!

320
00:23:51,907 --> 00:23:52,907
Okay.

321
00:23:53,873 --> 00:23:54,873
Later again.

322
00:24:13,601 --> 00:24:15,208
He’s taking so long to arrive.

323
00:24:27,503 --> 00:24:28,731
Look who finally showed up?

324
00:24:29,012 --> 00:24:31,514
What is it that you're
so excited about, ugly?

325
00:24:33,032 --> 00:24:35,057
You’re so annoying.
Sit down here.

326
00:24:35,081 --> 00:24:37,101
I told you,
I have something to tell you.

327
00:24:38,618 --> 00:24:40,211
I can’t contain my
excitement anymore.

328
00:24:40,235 --> 00:24:43,678
I need to let this out, ugly!

329
00:24:43,702 --> 00:24:45,037
You’re crazy again.

330
00:24:45,709 --> 00:24:48,534
Of course,
crazy in love with Chanwoo.

331
00:24:48,545 --> 00:24:51,115
So, we already met,
me and Chanwoo.

332
00:24:51,512 --> 00:24:52,512
You already met?

333
00:24:53,425 --> 00:24:55,428
Earlier.

334
00:24:55,452 --> 00:24:59,497
And it was so embarrassing
because he caught me.

335
00:25:00,048 --> 00:25:01,257
When you met?

336
00:25:01,257 --> 00:25:02,477
It was like this, like this.

337
00:25:02,501 --> 00:25:03,501
Come on, come on, come on.

338
00:25:03,544 --> 00:25:05,813
Stand up, stand up. Like this.

339
00:25:05,838 --> 00:25:07,006
There, hold me, hold me.

340
00:25:07,214 --> 00:25:08,549
Then pull me, okay.

341
00:25:30,415 --> 00:25:31,415
Was it like that?

342
00:25:32,089 --> 00:25:33,674
You got really close
to Chanwoo, huh.

343
00:25:35,215 --> 00:25:36,549
But not that long.

344
00:25:36,549 --> 00:25:39,204
Because I left right away
since Helga was there.

345
00:25:39,295 --> 00:25:41,607
And you know she told
me fangirling is not allowed.

346
00:25:41,631 --> 00:25:45,562
And before that happened,
she even asked me if I was a fan.

347
00:25:45,586 --> 00:25:50,174
Of course, I lied because I was
scared she might kick me out.

348
00:25:50,597 --> 00:25:52,891
Why would she kick you
out just for being a fan?

349
00:25:54,392 --> 00:25:55,910
Well, it’s done.
That’s what I said,

350
00:25:55,934 --> 00:25:56,978
I can’t take it back anymore.

351
00:26:01,900 --> 00:26:02,900
Oh.

352
00:26:03,109 --> 00:26:04,109
Sit down.

353
00:26:06,321 --> 00:26:07,321
George.

354
